Sounds good to me. I think we should provide an example without icon fonts, because then you have to explain how to include them and it gets complicated quickly. Therefore I suggest we just use the UTF-8 check mark. An average developer should know how to trade them for icon fonts or images. Here is a simple example I threw together quickly:

``` css
.markdown-body .task-list-item {
  position: relative;
}

.markdown-body .task-list-item input[type="checkbox"] {
  opacity: 0;
}

.markdown-body .task-list-item input[type="checkbox"] + label {
  display: block;
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: -24px;
  width: 16px;
  margin-top: -8px;
  height: 16px;
  border-radius: 2px;
  background: #CCC;
}

.markdown-body .task-list-item input[type="checkbox"]:checked + label::before {
  display: block;
  position: absolute;
  margin-top: -4px;
  margin-left: 2px;
  font-size: 1.2em;
  line-height: 1;
  border-radius: 2px;
  content: "✔";
  color: #1EBB52;
}
```

