That's a good point that we need to be careful with the tree rings when `transpose=True`.  The doc string for the `treering_center` parameter is currently:
```
    @param treering_center  A PositionD object with the center of the tree ring pattern in pixel
                            coordinates, which may be outside the pixel region. [default: None;
                            required if treering_func is provided]
```
which implies that it is in the coordinates of the actual image.  Not a transposed version.  So I think the current behavior is at least acting as documented.

So the question is really, is this the best API to have for this?  Should `treering_center` be in the transposed coordinates or the coordinates of the actual image being simulated?  

@jchiang87 Any thoughts on which way you thinks makes more sense?  Since you've actually used this feature in the wild.  Would it be more confusing to have `treering_center`'s (x,y) values refer to the transposed image (which I think is what is in the reference data)?  Or to have to swap (x,y) -> (y,x) when you pass it to Silicon along with `transpose=True`?

